metadata.description:

lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

- Press t: scale to screen size

metadata.name: Drawing a canvas #2
metadata.description:
In this artwork, chaos finds its harmony. Colored stripes move with seemingly random energy, yet they come together to form a pixelated tapestry that is both chaotic and ordered, a testament to the beauty of unpredictability.

This collection is a heartfelt tribute to the loyal NFT collectors who have been unwavering supporters of my creative journey. Each piece in this collection is a token of gratitude for the community that has stood by me from the beginning.

It was born out of the launch of my inaugural NFT collection on the Ethereum blockchain via Foundation. 

"The beauty of reflection" NFT release on Foundation: https://foundation.app/collection/presale

Created by VICIV, 2023.09

Libraries used: p5.js

Press "s" to save a high resoution png image

metadata.name: Flowers #245
metadata.description:
This project is inspired by natural flowers.
Flowers and foliage in the piece are arranged randomly, but they follow a regular pattern, as flowers do as they grow.
Initially, flowers are produced randomly and without color. Afterwards, the pieces are painted according to the color palettes, so that viewers can feel the effect of colors.
Each piece is processed until the frame part is reached.

Fully generated by p5.js

Press 's' to get a 3000x3000 px PNG file.

metadata.name: the endless dance #50
metadata.description:
“We thought of life by analogy with a journey, a pilgrimage, which had a serious purpose at the end, and the thing was to get to that end, success or whatever it is, maybe heaven after you’re dead. But we missed the point the whole way along. It was a musical thing and you were supposed to sing or to dance while the music was being played.” ― Alan Watts

Controls
spacebar: pause/unpause
mousedown: overdraw
x key: clear canvas

enjoy the dance

metadata.name: GuageTiles #10
metadata.description:
An interactive tiled pattern is generated with the fxhash which determines two features at random.

"groundsState" value determines a base configuration and is sampled uniformly at random in the range 0 to 1.

"spectralGap" determines the color of the pattern and comes in three types::
'low' (30%) is monochrome
'mid' (60%) is small hue range
'high' (10%) is a large hue range

*click/touch & hold/move* the canvas to charge the pattern and change the flux mode of the tiles.
*release* the canvas and the pattern decays back to its "groundState" value.

metadata.name: ThetaStar #17
metadata.description:
A "ThetaStar" is generated through an Iterated Function System determined by the fxhash with one main feature 'Theta' corresponding to an angle value in radians sampled uniformly at random in the range 2.5 < Theta < 3.0.

**Click / Touch** the canvas to reset and watch the "ThetaStar" gradually radiate in full spectrum.
The visually daring may **Rapidly Click / Touch** for an enhanced strobe like effect.
